          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-05-20 11:41:34" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to rise up in open defiance of authority, with the presumed intention to overthrow it or to act in complete opposition to its demands</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to rebel against</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to revolt</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to engage in insurrection</Gloss>
                <Gloss>rebellion</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is possible that ἀκαταστασία in {S:04202100900012} denotes merely unsettled conditions, but it is far more likely to carry the meaning of ‘insurrections’ and ‘revolts.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
